    "restricted": [],
    "regulated_minor": [
      "note: recipients under age of consent flow through the confidential fields above with a consent_age_gate marker in the dispatch payload. The gate is stored on the User row (user module) + read via cached recipient block. No column here is INHERENTLY minor-only."
    ],
    "regulated_health": [],
    "regulated_financial": [],
    "audit_log": [
      "audits.notifications.* rows produced by HasAuditable observers on NotificationTemplate (Publish + version changes), NotificationPreference (opt-in/opt-out trail), Notification (state transitions for compliance evidence)"
    ]
  },
  "notes": [
    "Notification.addressee_email + addressee_phone are DENORMALIZED from the User row into the Notification row at dispatch time \u2014 event-carried state. GDPR Art. 17 erasure anonymises them (`erased-<hash>@invalid.local`) but retains the row for aggregate compliance reporting.",
    "NotificationTemplate.body_rendered_html is `internal` because it's the compiled template with Blade placeholders (not final rendered output). Final rendered output is transient (never persisted).",
    "No `restricted` tier fields in core \u2014 credential-adjacent material (device tokens, provider API keys, SSO secrets) lives in channel modules or in tenants's integrations.",
    "NotificationDelivery.opened_ip is masked at rest (last octet zeroed) per foundation's audit_log convention."
  ]
